  "body": "Goal: a repeatable setup for a multi-client network. \n* Besu and geth at a minimum.\n* with metrics and logs\n\nKurtosis would be helpful with investigating peering behaviour.  It makes setting up multi-client networks really easy and repeatable.  \nhttps://github.com/kurtosis-tech/kurtosis-onboarding-experience/tree/master#kurtosis-ethereum-quickstart\nhttps://www.kurtosistech.com/\n\nThe only challenge is generating a non-trivial world state and chain that would take some time to sync.  \n\nOne way of bootstrapping non-trivial state:\nShadow forking goerli - https://github.com/skylenet/ethereum-genesis-generator/tree/goerli-shadow-fork\n\nbest way to contact them is on the Kurtosis-tech discord:\nhttps://discord.gg/HUapYX9RvV\n",
